# **LCB Specification ver0.1 (Eng)**

---

## 1. Document Overview

**Title:** Layered Coordinate Bitstream (LCB) Specification ver0.1
**Purpose:**
LCB provides a unified data layer for AI applications. It converts inputs from various sensors into a standardized, compressed, and streamable format.
Applications include surveillance, healthcare, autonomous driving, language processing, measurement/analysis, and environmental monitoring.

---

## 2. Core Structure

**LCB data flow:**

```
[Input Device/Sensor] → [Coordinate Mapping] → [Layering] → [Bitstream] → [Time-series Vector] → [Lightweight Inference]
```

### 2.1 Header & Footer

| Field       | Bits     | Description                             |
| ----------- | -------- | --------------------------------------- |
| Version     | 4        | LCB spec version                        |
| Type        | 4        | Data type (0=text,1=audio,2=utt,3=ctrl) |
| Timestamp   | 64       | Nanosecond timestamp                    |
| Source ID   | 16       | Device or speaker ID                    |
| Seq         | 32       | Sequence number                         |
| Layer Mask  | 16       | Selected layers to transmit             |
| Prev Hash   | 128      | Previous packet hash                    |
| Packet Hash | 128      | Current packet hash                     |
| Signature   | Variable | ECDSA or other digital signature        |

---

## 3. Generic Layer Definitions

| Layer | Content                                | Base Bits | Extension                            | Notes                                  |
| ----- | -------------------------------------- | --------- | ------------------------------------ | -------------------------------------- |
| L0    | Spatial coordinates (x,y,z)            | 12×3=36   | High-precision optional              | 1cm unit, coordinate system selectable |
| L1    | Attributes (color, temp, volume, etc.) | 4×4=16    | Add sensors freely                   | Normalized 0–1                         |
| L2    | Change vectors (Δx,Δy,Δz,Δattr)        | 5×4=20    | High-precision velocity/acceleration | Time-series gradient                   |
| L3    | Category/type                          | 6         | Custom tags                          | Human/Car/Plant/Building etc.          |
| L4    | Confidence                             | 3         | Extended metrics                     | 0–7                                    |
| L8    | Metadata                               | variable  | Hash, environment info               | e.g., device, session                  |

---

## 4. Language Data (LCB-Lang v0.1)

### 4.1 Layer Structure

| Layer | Content                                      | Base Bits | Extension                        | Notes                        |
| ----- | -------------------------------------------- | --------- | -------------------------------- | ---------------------------- |
| L0    | Time coordinates (frame start, duration)     | 64        | High-resolution optional         | ns unit                      |
| L1    | Acoustic features (volume, pitch, freq band) | 16        | Fine frequency resolution        | normalized 0–1               |
| L3    | Character/word/phoneme                       | variable  | Extended char/phoneme code       | UTF-8 mapping, dictionary ID |
| L7    | Emotion score                                | 8         | Composite emotional index        | joy/anger/sadness 0–255      |
| L8    | Metadata                                     | variable  | speaker ID, environment, session | Hash recommended             |

### 4.2 Document & Word-level Information

| Level    | Content                                          | Usage                                    |
| -------- | ------------------------------------------------ | ---------------------------------------- |
| Document | DocID, start/end, context tags                   | Multi-sentence analysis & inference      |
| Sentence | Phrase coordinates, sentence score, grammar tags | Cumulative emotion, style detection      |
| Word     | Word ID, dictionary ID, phoneme sequence, timing | Dictionary lookup, per-word emotion, TTS |

> **Note:** Dictionary creation is covered in a separate document. Word ID ↔ Dictionary ID mapping reduces model size.

---

## 5. Domain Templates

| Domain                    | Required Layers | Recommended Layers | Notes                                                  |
| ------------------------- | --------------- | ------------------ | ------------------------------------------------------ |
| Autonomous driving        | L0, L2, L3      | L1, L4             | Coordinates, velocity, type, confidence                |
| Healthcare / Surveillance | L0, L1, L4      | L3, L8             | Human body coordinates, attributes, metadata           |
| Measurement / Analysis    | L0, L1, L2      | L3                 | Building deterioration, plant growth, progress vectors |
| Language Processing       | L0, L1, L3      | L7, L8             | Speech/text/emotion/metadata                           |

---

## 6. Extension Field Usage

* Word ID: 16→32 bit expansion possible
* Emotion: 8→16 bit for detailed scoring
* Metadata: Add session, environment sensor info
* Layer Mask: Selective transmission, lightweight transfer

---

## 7. Compression & Tamper Protection

* zlib compression
* Hash chaining (Prev Hash / Packet Hash)
* ECDSA signatures for packet verification
* Anonymous hash (speaker/device ID)

---

## 8. Implementation Guidance

* **This doc:** Data structures, bit allocations, layer definitions
* **Separate doc:** Dictionary creation, Word ID ↔ Dict ID, preprocessing, demo code
* Allows standardized specification + implementation flexibility.

